ke account of expected future cost and activity pressures, for example anticipated changes in population size, demographics as well as inflation in health and care provision costs (as reflected in national planning assumptions).</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","1573 ; 1579 ; 1580 ; 1582","2017-07-06T15:02:24.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746277/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746277/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746277/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-28","Health Services: Dudley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what provisions for break clauses are included in the contract proposed by Dudley Clinical Commissioning Group for a multi-speciality community provider.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","1585"
