"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746361","Department of Health","false","2017-07-03","<p>Lord Dennis Stevenson and Paul Farmer are progressing their independent review on how employers can better support all employees, including those with mental ill-health or poor well-being, to remain and thrive in work. The review is due to report later this year.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-07-03T13:39:25.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746361/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746361/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746361/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-28","Mental Health: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the Government plans to publish its review of mental health practices in the workplace.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","1686"
