ospital Birmingham;</p><p>- University Hospital Bristol.</p><p> </p><p>Some of these centres would have provided treatments for AVMs and trigeminal neuralgia.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","1598","2017-07-05T09:57:51.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746362/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746362/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746362/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-28","Radiotherapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, prior to 2016, which hospitals in England used stereotactic radiosurgery to treat cerebral arteriovenous malformations and trigeminal neuralgia.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","1599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746363","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-07","<p>Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force. During this period the Government will continue to negotiate, implement and apply EU legislation.</p><p>There are presently 15 EU directives relating to the Department for Transport which await transposition into UK law before 29 March 2019.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-07T08:15:44.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746363/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746363/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-28","Department for Transport: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many EU directives relating to his Department are being transposed into UK law.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","1704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746364","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-07","<p>Government policy and legal assessment remain to ensure full compliance with EU legal requirements until the UK leaves the EU. This includes transposition of EU directives.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-07T08:08:50.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746364/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746364/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-28","Department for Transport: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when his Department plans to stop transposing new EU directives into UK law.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","1705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746365","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy negotiates on behalf of the UK in respect to EU legislation covering single market, energy, consumer rights, labour markets, research and innovation.</p><p>The Department provides Explanatory Memoranda to Parliament, on proposals defined by the terms of reference of the parliamentary EU scrutiny committees, which can be found online.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-04T15:24:31.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746365/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746365/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-28","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many new EU directives relating to his Department's responsibilities are in negotiation in the EU.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","1706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746366","Home Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>Intelligence exchange between UK law enforcement and Europol is well-established and routine, including on organised immigration crime. The National Crime Agency and Immigration Enforcement also support Europol with seconded staff, including within the European Migrant Smuggling Centre (EMSC), which incorporates JOT Mare. This cooperation has and continues to assist UK efforts to tackle organised immigration crime impacting on the UK.</p><p>However, the data requested is not held centrally and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","1711 ; 1719 ; 1724","2017-07-05T15:13:23.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746366/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746366/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746366/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-28","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on how many occasions the UK accessed information from Europol's European Migrant Smuggling Centre in each year since that centre's creation.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","1713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746367","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-03","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-03T16:03:35.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746367/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746367/answer","PQ1748 v0.7.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ1748","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746367/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-28","EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent estimate he has made of the number of non-UK EU nationals living in (a) the UK, (b) the North East and (c) Newcastle-upon-Tyne.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746368","Department of Health","false","2017-07-03","<p>There have been no prescriptions for Valium issued since 2010. Valium is a brand name for the drug diazepam and the brand is not allowed to be prescribed in National Health Service primary care.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-07-03T14:48:43.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746368/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746368/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746368/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-28","Diazepam: Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prescriptions for valium have been issued in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","1734"
